  en:{title:"Memory Box (Continuing Bonds)", about:"A symbolic tool in grief therapy based on the 'continuing bonds' theory (Klass, Silverman & Nickman, 1996).", purpose:"To carry the connection with the person who was lost forward in a new, portable form, rather than 'cutting it off.'", usage:"Photos, objects, and written memories are gathered and kept in a symbolic box or book.", outcomes:"Eases the grieving process and preserves a positive bond to the loss."},
